{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fe359e59-3a1d-42ea-8ab8-1f99e668f6db","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform, VSTest options move behind `--` using the new switch names:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to your test project):\n\n| Old mechanism | New package |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` |\n\n`--filter` is still handled by `dotnet test` itself, so it stays before the `--` separator.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bd38e0eb-0d4e-44e6-9e41-07acf87960b6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter`  (same, actually)\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--collect-coverage` with format options (or using Microsoft.CodeCoverage)\n- `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang` and `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` becomes `--hangdump` with `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\n\n- When using `dotnet test` with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the filter flag passes through unchanged, but the TRX reporting requires the TrxReport extension package, and code coverage collection needs to be configured through the newer Microsoft.CodeCoverage package instead of the legacy format. I need to clarify how `dotnet test` interacts with Microsoft.Testing.Platform—`--filter` stays with `dotnet test` itself, while platform-specific options like `--report-trx`, `--coverage`, and the dump options go after `--`. Let me work through the exact command structure and option mappings. I'm verifying that each option requires its corresponding NuGet package extension, and the command structure looks correct for running integration tests with comprehensive diagnostics.","outputTokens":1259,"requestId":"BC2B:2BEA6E:1CACDD3:1FBFC3A:69FA90A2"},"id":"f0da41dc-7840-41ce-affd-c26c489d6442","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:52:06.112Z","parentId":"4038663f-6169-4df0-82ad-0d2b843aaade"}
